-- Bernheim Wants Generali's Honorary Chairman Position, Corriere Sera Says
-- Armorel Kenna
-- 2010-04-23T06:23:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-23/bernheim-wants-generali-s-honorary-chairman-position-corriere-sera-says.html

          
          
             Antoine Bernheim would be “very
happy” to accept the role of Assicurazioni Generali SpA
honorary chairman, daily Corriere della Sera said, citing an
interview.  
 Bernheim, Generali’s outgoing chairman, isn’t included in
the list of board members that will be reviewed at the insurer’s
annual meeting tomorrow.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
